P_HTM[2036]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca cetasovinibandhā.**These are the five emotional shackles.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ cetasovinibandhānaṃ pahānāya ime cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā.**To give up these five emotional shackles you should develop the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[2038]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2039]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[2040]="*vīriyasamādhi …**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[2041]="*cittasamādhi …**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[2042]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[2043]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ cetasovinibandhānaṃ pahānāya ime cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā”ti.**To give up these five emotional shackles you should develop these four bases of psychic power.”*";
P_HTM[2044]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2045]="*Iddhipādavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[2046]="*Yatheva satipaṭṭhānā,* **";
P_HTM[2047]="*padhānā caturopi ca;* **";
P_HTM[2048]="*Cattāro iddhipādā ca,* **";
P_HTM[2049]="*tatheva sampayojayeti.* **";
P_HTM[2050]="*1(10) 5. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed*";
P_HTM[2051]="*1(10) 5. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**93*";
P_HTM[2052]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya nava dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, nine things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[2053]="*Katame nava?**What nine?*";
P_HTM[2054]="*Asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā, aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, virāgasaññā—**The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness of food, dissatisfaction with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, not-self in suffering, giving up, and fading away.*";
P_HTM[2055]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime nava dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these nine things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[2056]="*1(10) 5. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed*";
P_HTM[2057]="*1(10) 5. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**94*";
P_HTM[2058]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya nava dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, nine things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[2059]="*Katame nava?**What nine?*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ, dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ, catutthaṃ jhānaṃ, ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ, viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ, ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ, saññāvedayitanirodho—**The first absorption, the second absorption, the third absorption, the fourth absorption, the dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of nothingness, the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, and the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[2061]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime nava dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these nine things should be developed.”*";
